nz in einer letztlich erfolgreichen Diskursgeschichte, die bis zum preußischen „Emanzipationsedikt“ (1812) führten, herausgearbeitet. Die Auswertung der „Judenbilder“ heute kaum noch bekannter preußischer Beamter ermöglicht neue Einblicke in die Emanzipationsgeschichte der Juden im Preußen der Zeitenwende vom 18. zum 19. Jahrhundert.  aThe road to full legal equality was a long one for the Jews of Prussia. The focus of this study is on the history of conflict and dialogue between representatives of the Jewish community and Prussian administrative authorities. By examining the history of this discourse, the study casts light on the limitations and possibilities of tolerance in what ultimately proved to be a successful historical negotiation, culminating in the Prussian “Emancipation Edict” of 1812.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aJewsxCivil rightszGermanyzPrussiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewsxEmancipationzGermanyzPrussiaxHistory. 0aJewsxLegal status, laws, etczGermanyzPrussiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewsxLegal status, laws, etc.zGermanyzPrussiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewszGermanyzPrussiaxHistoryy19th century. 4a19. Jahrhundert. 4aEmanzipation. 4aJuden. 4aPreußen. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  a19th century, emancipation, Jews, Prussia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS0 cprintz978311030562340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030603340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110306033423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110306033/original  a